						               													<description>Mimo is a game with 50 cards (30 actions and 20 animals).&amp;#10;It rempliments classic games like Charades and Memory.&amp;#10;In the first game a player draws one card and acts it: who guesses the action/animal earns the card and becomes the new actor.&amp;#10;The second game is similar to the first one, but there are 12 cards on the board face up: the actor secretly choose 1 card and the others have to pick the right one.&amp;#10;In the third game the active player has to act all the already drawn cards in the right order. If a player makes a mistake, he takes the turned over cards as penalty.&amp;#10;In the last game, players choose in turn the cards on the board, acting them: then, they have to guess which cards the opponents have, acting them again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
